<!DOCTYPE learningAssessment SYSTEM "../dtd/learningAssessment.dtd">
<learningAssessment id="learningAssessment_bx3_wm2_hk">
  <title>Multiple Correct DITA 1.3 Test</title>
  <learningAssessmentbody>
    <lcIntro>This Multiple Correct question tests the following:<ul id="ul_d3s_rv2_hk">
        <li>Question stem has multiple block elements (&lt;p> and &lt;fig>)</li>
        <li>Question incorrect feedback has multiple block elements (&lt;p> and
          &lt;simpletable>)</li>
      </ul></lcIntro>
        <lcInteraction>
      <lcMultipleSelect2>
        <lcQuestion2> The following chart plots the per-share prices of EcoCorp and TeleCorp stock
          at the beginning of each of the first seven months during year  <i>X</i> . <p>
            <fig>
              <image href="chart.jpg" id="image_bkl_lv2_hk"/>
            </fig>
          </p><p> Based on the chart, over the course of which months did the per-share price of
            EcoCorp stock either increase or decrease by more than two dollars?</p><p> Indicate 
              <u>all</u>  such months.  </p></lcQuestion2>
        <lcAnswerOptionGroup2 id="lcAnswerOptionGroup2_cfm_n52_hk">
          <lcAnswerOption2>
            <lcAnswerContent2>January</lcAnswerContent2>
            <lcCorrectResponse2/>
          </lcAnswerOption2>
          <lcAnswerOption2>
            <lcAnswerContent2>February</lcAnswerContent2>
            <lcCorrectResponse2/>
          </lcAnswerOption2>
          <lcAnswerOption2>
            <lcAnswerContent2>March</lcAnswerContent2>
          </lcAnswerOption2>
          <lcAnswerOption2>
            <lcAnswerContent2>April</lcAnswerContent2>
          </lcAnswerOption2>
          <lcAnswerOption2>
            <lcAnswerContent2>May</lcAnswerContent2>
            <lcCorrectResponse2/>
          </lcAnswerOption2>
          <lcAnswerOption2>
            <lcAnswerContent2>June</lcAnswerContent2>
            <lcCorrectResponse2/>
          </lcAnswerOption2>
        </lcAnswerOptionGroup2>
        <lcFeedbackIncorrect2>EcoCorp stock either increased or decreased by more than two dollars
          in January, February, May, and June, as follows:<simpletable frame="all"
            relcolwidth="1.0* 1.0*" id="simpletable_ngz_fw2_hk">
            <sthead>
              <stentry>Month</stentry>
              <stentry>Change</stentry>
            </sthead>
            <strow>
              <stentry>January</stentry>
              <stentry>-4</stentry>
            </strow>
            <strow>
              <stentry>February</stentry>
              <stentry>+3.5</stentry>
            </strow>
            <strow>
              <stentry>May</stentry>
              <stentry>-4</stentry>
            </strow>
            <strow>
              <stentry>June</stentry>
              <stentry>-2.5</stentry>
            </strow>
          </simpletable><p>In March, the stock increased by about one dollar, while in April, the
            increase was about one and a half dollars. </p><p>Telecorp stock had changes of more
            than two dollars in January and May only.</p></lcFeedbackIncorrect2>
      </lcMultipleSelect2>
    </lcInteraction>
  </learningAssessmentbody>
